{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We examine the effects of image classification filters in several application domains in order to gain insight into their use and effects on road anomalies classification.In [27], for example, a new descriptor for object and scene image categorization based on the Gabor wavelet transformation was developed.",
    "The Gabor descriptor was concatenated with the Pyramid of Histogram of Oriented Gradients for all of the filtered images with different orientations (PHOG).",
    "Six diverse colour spaces were used to evaluate the performance of the proposed novel Gabor-Pyramid of Histogram of Oriented Gradients (GPHOG) on some of the colour spaces discovered.",
    "To minimise dimensionality in the six colour spaces, Principal Component Analysis (PCA) was performed, yielding a unique Fused Color Gabor-Pyramid of Histogram of Oriented Gradients (FC-GPHOG) descriptor.",
    "To extract features, the Enhanced Fisher model and Nearest Neighbor were utilised."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
